07-08 March - Ricotta Ravioli

Dough
- 6 cup flour
- 6 tablespoon Crisco
- 6 teaspoon baking powder
- 2 cup sugar*
- 6 room temperature eggs
- 1 teaspoon lemon zest (optional)
- 1 package Bertolini Lievito (optional)**
- 1 package powder vanilla or 2 tablespoon liquid vanilla

Filling

- 1   lb Ricotta 
- 1   package powder vanilla or 1 tablespoon vanilla 
- 1   cup confectioners sugar
- 3/4 cup mini chocolate chips
- ?   tsp cinnamon (optional) (editor's note: hole punch completely through this number)

Sift flour and combine with Crisco till mixed. Add baking powder and vanilla (if using powder). Beat eggs, sugar and liquid vanilla. Mix dry ingredients with wet ingredients to form dough. Let rest. Mix filling ingredients and refrigerate to meld flavors together. 

Make ravioli = 350F oven. Bake 8-12 minutes until lightly golden. Sprinkle with powdered sugar and serve. 

I used the dough recipe to make Easter Egg cookies, came out very good. Hold their shape. 

* I used only 1 1/2 cup sugar. I thought 2 cups was a little too sweet 
** you can get this at Sclafani bakery $1.25 a package